<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.278831>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 – 9. Eilica pomposa Keyserling, 1891. 1. Male, Left palpus, ventral view. 2. Female, dorsal view. 3. Female, detail, sternum. 4. Female, carapace, anterior view. 5. Epigynum, detail, ventral view. 6. Epigynum, ventral view; clarified. 7. Epigynum, dorsal view; clarified. 8. Epigynum, ventral view; drawing. 9. Epyginum, dorsal view; drawing. Scale bar: (8, 9) 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/278831/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

